	abstract = {In order to raise the awareness of design and to advance the design ability in the textile manufacturing industry, it is important to improve the design skills of new designers through education. The paper investigates into the unique characteristics of European textile design education through various research methods such as observation, questionnaire, and focus group to gather quality first hand data. Though the result of a small group (10 selected students) teaching experiment, the research develops a teaching model for textile-design education, which can be adaptable to the textile-design industry. Based on the previous research, the researcher continues to test the new developed model for textile-design in two related courses with different number of students (26 students in Fashion Design course and 56 in Dyeing & Testing course). The result shows that the students develop unique design ability that combines technology and creativity, which in terms to validate the proposed teaching model to be a success. Nevertheless, due to the decrease of teaching hours and the increasing numbers of the students, the overall performance of student creativity might fall off to a certain degree.},
